cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.PF 

This paper deals with the analysis of dynamic membership in structured peer-to-peer networks, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the performance and consistency of lookups under churn, which is a networking issue (cs.NI). The use of a fluid model approach and the analysis of network disconnection probability and failed successor and finger pointers are topics related to simulation and modeling (cs.SI). The paper also deals with structured overlays, which is a topic related to data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the Chord system, which is a specific implementation of a structured overlay, making cs.PF a likely sub-category as well.
